{"key":"post-6459080","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6459080</id>\n<content>Fungi are a totally different organism from plants.  Nobody can answer your question in detail without writing a book.  In short, mushrooms don't 'conduct' moisture up into them the way plants channel water.  Mushrooms grow by cell division, and have a mycelial network, but no vascular or similar systems.  A common mistake is to think the mushroom is analogous to a plant, and the mycelium analogous to the roots.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6459311</next>\n<prev>6458860</prev>\n<first>6306864</first>\n<last>6459311</last>\n<when>1168813108</when>\n<utime>01/15/07 12:18 AM</utime>\n</post>"}